Increase prevalence of thyroid autoimmunity is found in patients with chronic urticaria.

 About 5-34% of chronic urticaria patients is associated with the presence of thyroid autoimmunity who are euthyroid status whereas 5-10% of them with either hyperthyroidism or hypothyroidism.

